These are Puzzles for 4x4 Level 3

.:: Puzzle 4x4-Level-3-1::.
City: new-york, liverpool, hannover, san-francisco
There 4 different types of food: apple, banana, grapes, pineapple
The people have 4 different jobs:  san-franciscocher, dressmaker, mechanic, social-worker
The people use 4 different means of transport: quad-bike, ship, tram, van
 1. the person eating banana is on the left or right of the person driving the ship##3
 2. the person traveling to liverpool is the person eating pineapple##1
 3. the person driving the quad-bike is on the far left or far right##3
 4. the person driving the tram is on the right of the person traveling to liverpool##1
 5. the person driving the quad-bike is on the far left or far right##3
 6. the person eating grapes is on the left or right of the san-franciscocher##3
 7. the person traveling to hannover is on the left of the person traveling to liverpool##1
 8. the person traveling to san-francisco is on the right of the person eating grapes##1
 9. the person driving the quad-bike is on the far left##1
10. the mechanic is on the right of the dressmaker##1
11. the dressmaker is on the left of the person traveling to new-york##1

.:: Answer ::.
|             |     1     |     2      |      3      |   4   |
| City    | hannover   | liverpool       | new-york | san-francisco   |
| Food        | banana    | pineapple  | grapes      | apple |
| Job         | social-worker      | dressmaker | mechanic         | san-franciscocher   |
| Transport   | quad-bike | ship       | tram        | van   |

